CNN¶

In [31]:
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Conv1D, MaxPooling1D, Flatten, Dense, MaxPooling2D
In [32]:
#  CNN 
cnn = Sequential()
cnn.add(Conv1D(filters=32, kernel_size=3, activation='relu', input_shape=(X_train.shape[1], 1)))
cnn.add(MaxPooling1D(pool_size=2))
cnn.add(Flatten())
cnn.add(Dense(units=50, activation='relu'))
cnn.add(Dense(units=1))

# 
cnn.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='mean_squared_error')

cnn.summary()

Model evaluation¶

In [37]:
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, mean_absolute_error, r2_score, explained_variance_score
In [38]:
res = []
for item in ["RandomForest", "RNN", "CNN"]:
    # 1. Mean Squared Error
    mse = mean_squared_error(eva_df["True radio"], eva_df[item])

    # 2. Root Mean Squared Error
    rmse = np.sqrt(mse)

    # 3. Mean Absolute Error
    mae = mean_absolute_error(eva_df["True radio"], eva_df[item])

    # 4. Coefficient of Determination
    r2 = r2_score(eva_df["True radio"], eva_df[item])

    # 5. Explained Variance Score
    explained_variance = explained_variance_score(eva_df["True radio"], eva_df[item])
    
    res.append([mse, rmse, mae, r2, explained_variance])
In [39]:
# dataframe
evaluation = pd.DataFrame(res, columns=['MSE', 'RMSE', 'MAE', 'R Score', 'EVS'], 
                          index=["RandomForest", "RNN", "CNN"])
